    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-09-19T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-09-19T03:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <head>325. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Lebanon</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d325fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 783A.00/9–1958. Top Secret; Priority. Repeated to London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-09-19T11:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 19, 1958—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1627. Repeated London Exclusive for Admiral <persName corresp="#p_HAJLJ1"
                        >Holloway</persName>. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1273<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d325fn2">
                        <ref target="#d322">Document 322</ref>.</note> I believe we should retain
                    initiative in announcing withdrawal of all US forces from Lebanon by October 15
                    in order to forestall adverse propaganda possibilities outlined <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1560.<note n="3" xml:id="d325fn3">
                        <ref target="#d319">Document 319</ref>.</note> However, I believe we could
                    usefully arrange with <persName corresp="#p_CGF2">Chehab</persName> and Prime
                    Minister of new government for a joint US–Lebanon release outlining details of
                    this phased withdrawal.</p>
                <p>I do not consider it either feasible or desirable to work out some announcement
                    with <persName corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName>: (A) Because <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName> himself is deeply opposed to early
                    withdrawal of US forces; and (B) an announcement involving ex-president would
                    not sit well with new president.</p>
                <pb facs="0606" n="574" xml:id="pg_574"/>
                <p>Re final paragraph reference telegram, it is unnecessary to stress to <persName
                        corresp="#p_CGF2">Chehab</persName> that withdrawal take place in logical,
                    dignified and orderly fashion since this has been general’s concept from the
                    beginning. Throughout many conversations Admiral <persName corresp="#p_HAJLJ1"
                        >Holloway</persName> and I have had with <persName corresp="#p_CGF2"
                        >Chehab</persName> he has shown a soldier’s appreciation of need for phased
                    movement and full comprehension withdrawal must take place in an orderly fashion
                    with maximum of cooperation from Lebanese Government and armed forces.</p>
                <p>Recommendation: That I be authorized to negotiate with <persName
                        corresp="#p_CGF2">Chehab</persName> tentative text of a joint communiqué
                    indicating, however, that initial release will come from US side either from
                    Washington or <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_UNGA1">UNGA</gloss>.</p>
                <p>General Adams, Admirals Loud and <persName corresp="#p_YRAHA1">Yeager</persName>
                    concur.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MCRM1">
                            <hi rend="strong">McClintock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
